                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6283: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-16T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 16, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 16—5:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>441. Department’s 159, May 15, 5 p.m.<note n="40" xml:id="d357fn40">Not printed;
                        it requested additional information regarding protection of life and
                        property by other governments.</note> Action taken limited to Tungchow and
                    immediate neighborhood. Americans chiefly involved. I have had no information
                    regarding other nationalities. We were chiefly concerned about children in
                    American school at Tungchow, Peiping city and neighborhood quiet. It has not
                    seemed necessary to consider precautionary steps here as no immediate danger
                    expected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
